Mike,  Having--not by choice beleive me--served with in one capacity or another, foreign military, I did pick up some knowledge and never condemed the American troops for their attitude.<br>
Generally, we don't take the time to educated our troops on the cultural of the country.  This applies to FAOs as well in my experience in Latin America.  <br>
We also never take the time to try and get our troops involved with the locals.  Too bad.  Our troops are or can be the best advertisement for America.  I bleive that.<br>
I was sittting in the bar at the Ft. Benning Off. Club in 1970 when I heard two Inf. Col.s bad-mouthing ARVN.  <br>
I tore them a new asshole--basicly with what I wrote above but with a lot of basic Anglo Saxon.<br>
I was a Ltc. at the time, but they didn't say diddly back to me.<br>
Born Nick---the Army changed it to Andy.<br>
So---it;s Andy.<br>

